\description{
Single source-of-truth for the column structure of
\code{pdactrace_reference}. v0.4.0 widened the trajectory classifier to
a 12-template competitive catalog (Early × 4 + Mid × 4 + Late × 2 +
Monotonic × 2). The atlas surface still restricts visible
\code{rna_pattern} / \code{prot_pattern} calls to \strong{Early × 4 only} — Mid /
Late / Monotonic best-matches are flagged via \code{excluded_mid_pattern},
\code{excluded_late_pattern}, \code{excluded_monotonic_pattern} for transparent
provenance.
}
\details{
Design scope: pdactrace is a \emph{resectable-stage marker discovery}
atlas. Including all 12 templates in the matching step is a
deliberate design choice — a gene must out-compete 11 alternatives
(Mid + Late + Monotonic best-matches) before it is surfaced as Early.
This widens the negative-evidence pool (e.g., GAPDH and CDH13 are
correctly demoted to Monotonic_Up under v0.4.0) and strengthens the
resectable-stage relevance of surfaced Early calls.

Layers:
\itemize{
\item \strong{identifiers} - gene_symbol, ensembl_id, entrez_id
\item \strong{rna}         - DESeq2 LRT padj + per-stage Wald padj (v0.4.0) +
4 stage coefficients + 12-template best-match
(surfaced only if Early × 4) + Pearson rho +
Stouffer + 3 \verb{excluded_*_pattern} flags
\item \strong{protein}     - tissue protein 12-template (surfaced if Early × 4) +
Tier1/Tier2 + RNA-protein concordance flag
\item \strong{scrna}       - dominant cell origin + full distribution +
hypergeom enrichment padj
\item \strong{serum}       - detected flag + log2FC PDAC/Pan/HC +
translation_class A/B/C
\item \strong{clinical}    - resectable_marker / panel_member flags
\item \strong{provenance}  - source phase script names + last_updated +
evidence_scope
\item \strong{t3_ready}    - detectability / direction labels + features +
model_trainable + model_card_ref (NA in T2.5)
}
}
